column1: {"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:217"],"Definition":"A phyllome that subtends a reproductive structure.","Source_ID":"PO:0009055","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"bract"}
{"Definition":"A cork cambium (PO:0005599) that is part of a root (PO:0009005).","Source_ID":"PO:0025436","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"root cork cambium"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:244"],"Definition":"A portion of parenchyma tissue that is part of a connective and projects into a pollen sac.","Source_ID":"PO:0020005","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"placentoid"}

{"Synonyms":["fusiform initial"],"Definition":"An elongated cambial initial cell (PO:0000295) with approximately wedge-shaped ends that is part of the vascular cambium (PO:0005598) and gives rise to axial cells.","Source_ID":"PO:0000079","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"fusiform initial cell"}
{"Definition":"A lower glume that is part of an ear spikelet.","Source_ID":"PO:0006369","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"lower glume of ear spikelet"}

{"Definition":"Stage of gynoecium development defined by differentiation and expansion of carpels.","Source_ID":"PO:0004501","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"gynoecium differentiation and expansion stage"}

{"Synonyms":["OB_SF_PO:3272612","archegonial head"],"Definition":"An umbrella-shaped cardinal organ part that is the apical portion of an archegoniophore and bears archegonia.","Source_ID":"PO:0030076","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"archegonium head"}

{"Definition":"The stage at which leaves at ten nodes, other than the cotyledonary node, are visible above ground.","Source_ID":"PO:0007103","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"LP.10 ten leaves visible stage"}
{"Definition":"OBSOLETE. A primordium that will develop into a flower.","Source_ID":"PO:0004706","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"flower primordium"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:575","phyllome anlagen cell"],"Definition":"A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is part of the phyllome anlagen (PO:0025430).","Source_ID":"PO:0025586","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"phyllome founder cell"}

{"Synonyms":["embryonic plant cell","PO_GIT:281"],"Definition":"A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).","Source_ID":"PO:0025028","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"embryo plant cell"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:539"],"Definition":"Stage during which the four clearly defined locules are established. All anther cell types present and microspore mother cells appear.","Source_ID":"PO:0001026","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"D locules established stage"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:546"],"Definition":"A floral organ formation stage (PO:0025585) which begins with the differentiation of floral organs (PO:0025395) from the floral organ primordium (PO:0025477) and ends with the beginning of the flowering stage (PO:0007616).","Source_ID":"PO:0007600","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"floral organ differentiation stage"}
{"Definition":"The margin of a cotyledon.","Source_ID":"PO:0025012","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"cotyledon margin"}

{"Synonyms":["cambial initial","cambial cell"],"Definition":"An initial cell (PO:0004011) that is part of the vascular cambium (PO:0005598) or cork cambium (PO:0005599), and by periclinal divisions, produces cells to the outside or inside of the cambial axis.","Source_ID":"PO:0000295","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"cambial initial cell"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:343","embryonic mesocotyl"],"Definition":"A mesocotyl (PO:0020037) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).","Source_ID":"PO:0025294","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"embryo mesocotyl"}
{"Definition":"The flag leaf sheath has started to extend.","Source_ID":"PO:0007018","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"BO.01 early boot stage"}

{"Synonyms":["third order paraclade","PO_GIT:264","fourth order inflorescence axis","tertiary inflorescence branch"],"Definition":"An inflorescence branch (PO:0009081) arising from a second order inflorescence branch (PO:0006322).","Source_ID":"PO:0025105","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"third order inflorescence branch"}
{"Definition":"A shoot apex that has as part a reproductive shoot apical meristem.","Source_ID":"PO:0025222","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"reproductive shoot apex"}

{"Definition":"A ground meristem (PO:0025594) that gives rise to a portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059) in the shoot system (PO:0009006).","Source_ID":"PO:0025595","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"shoot system ground meristem"}
{"Definition":"The stage at which the first flower(s) open.","Source_ID":"PO:0007026","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"FL.00 first flower(s) open stage"}
{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:538","PO_GIT:69"],"Definition":"A plant structure (PO:0005679) which is a whole organism.","Source_ID":"PO:0000003","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"whole plant"}

{"Synonyms":["tuber branch","PO_GIT:127","shoot axis branch tuber"],"Definition":"A tuber (PO:0025522) that develops from a branch (PO:0025073).","Source_ID":"PO:0004543","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"shoot axis tuber"}
{"Definition":"Pulvinus of the petiole.","Source_ID":"PO:0009111","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"petiole pulvinus"}

{"Synonyms":["bract primordia","PO_GIT:466","portion of bract primordium tissue"],"Definition":"A phyllome primordium (PO:0025487) that is committed to the development of a flower bract (PO:0009055).","Source_ID":"PO:0025487","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"bract primordium"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:168","strobili","PO_GIT:601"],"Definition":"A reproductive shoot system (PO:0025082) consisting of a number of sporophylls (PO:0009026) or plant ovule (PO:0020003)-bearing modified leaves (PO:0025034) grouped terminally on a stem (PO:0009047).","Source_ID":"PO:0025083","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"strobilus"}
{"Definition":"A portion of plant tissue that is a flap-like projection of the coleorhiza, inserted opposite the scutellum.","Source_ID":"PO:0020036","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"epiblast"}

{"Synonyms":["tuber bud","PO_GIT:102"],"Definition":"An axillary vegetative bud (PO:0004712) that is part of a shoot axis tuber (PO:0004543).","Source_ID":"PO:0025040","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"shoot axis tuber axillary vegetative bud"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:111"],"Definition":"A portion of shoot axis epidermis (PO:0000112) that is part of a stem (PO:0009047).","Source_ID":"PO:0025178","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"stem epidermis"}
{"Definition":"A portion of shoot system epidermis (PO:0006035) that is part of a shoot axis (PO:0025029).","Source_ID":"PO:0000112","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"shoot axis epidermis"}

{"Synonyms":["root primordia","portion of root primordium tissue","PO_GIT:467"],"Definition":"A primordium (PO:0025127) that develops from a root anlagen (PO:0025433) and is committed to the development of a root (PO:0009005).","Source_ID":"PO:0005029","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"root primordium"}
{"Definition":"A phyllome apex PO:0025139) that is part of a tepal (PO:0009033).","Source_ID":"PO:0025143","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"tepal apex"}
{"Definition":"A cork cambium (PO:0005599) that is part of a shoot axis (PO:0025029).","Source_ID":"PO:0025435","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"shoot axis cork cambium"}
{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:380"],"Definition":"A small flower (PO:0009046) that is part of a spikelet (PO:0009051).","Source_ID":"PO:0009082","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"spikelet floret"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:374"],"Definition":"An inflorescence detectable phase during which an inflorescence has reached at its full length.","Source_ID":"PO:0007003","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"IL.03 full inflorescence length reached stage"}
{"Definition":"A lower glume that is part of a tassel spikelet.","Source_ID":"PO:0006372","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"lower glume of tassel spikelet"}
{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:232"],"Definition":"A phyllome trichome that is part of a leaf epidermis.","Source_ID":"PO:0006504","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"leaf trichome"}
{"Definition":"A terminal reproductive bud develops into an inflorescence.","Source_ID":"PO:0004715","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"terminal inflorescence bud"}
{"Definition":"A tuber axillary bud meristem that is part of an aerial tuber.","Source_ID":"PO:0025069","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"aerial tuber axillary bud meristem"}

{"Synonyms":["sporphyte phase","sporophytic phase","sporophytic development stage","OBO-SF2_PO:139"],"Definition":"A whole plant development stage (PO:0007033) that has as primary participant a whole plant (PO:0000003) during the interval between fertilization (or apogamy) and death.","Source_ID":"PO:0028002","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"sporophyte development stage"}

{"Synonyms":["stomia"],"Definition":"A plant anatomical space that is a slit in an anther lobe formed from when a dehiscence zone dehisces.","Source_ID":"PO:0020101","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"stomium"}
{"Definition":"A lateral root cap that is part of a root cap of lateral root.","Source_ID":"PO:0003020","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"lateral root cap of lateral root"}
{"Definition":"OBSOLETE. The stage at which the meristem of the crown root becomes evident.","Source_ID":"PO:0007514","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"B3 crown root meristem formation"}
{"Definition":"OBSOLETE. Third layer of sexine.","Source_ID":"PO:0020015","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"sculpture elements"}
{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:323"],"Definition":"A plant callus (PO:0005052) grown or maintained in vitro.","Source_ID":"PO:0000009","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"cultured plant callus"}
{"Definition":"A terminal reproductive bud that develops into a strobilus.","Source_ID":"PO:0025077","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"terminal strobilus bud"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:161","tap root"],"Definition":"A root (PO:0009005) that develops directly from an seedling radicle (PO:0020127).","Source_ID":"PO:0020127","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"primary root"}
{"Definition":"A sieve cell (PO:0025415) that is part of a portion of secondary phloem (PO:0005043).","Source_ID":"PO:0025456","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"secondary phloem sieve cell"}

{"Definition":"OBSOLETE. Radial expansion followed by subsequent periclinal divisions forms the isodiametric founder cell tissues.","Source_ID":"PO:0007530","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"A2.3 founder cell derivatives of lateral root"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:141","microgamete","male gamete"],"Definition":"A gamete (PO:0025006) produced by an antheridium (PO:0025125) or a microgametophyte (PO:0025280).","Source_ID":"PO:0000084","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"plant sperm cell"}

{"Synonyms":["root tuber","storage root","PO_GIT:47"],"Definition":"A tuber (PO:0004543) that develops from a tuberous root (PO:0025523) and is further radially enlarged.","Source_ID":"PO:0025476","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"tuberous root tuber"}
{"Definition":"Stage of calyx development defined by differentiation and expansion of sepal.","Source_ID":"PO:0001044","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"sepal differentiation and expansion stage"}

{"Synonyms":["portion of protoxylem tissue","PO_GIT:434"],"Definition":"A portion of primary xylem (PO:0000272) tissue that has as part one or more protoxylem tracheary elements (PO:0025575) embedded in parenchyma (PO:0005421) tissue.","Source_ID":"PO:0000272","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"protoxylem"}

{"Synonyms":["first order paraclade","PO_GIT:264","second order inflorescence axis"],"Definition":"An inflorescence branch (PO:0009081) arising from a first order inflorescence axis (PO:0025104).","Source_ID":"PO:0006321","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"primary inflorescence branch"}

{"Synonyms":["sporophyte senescence stage","PO_GIT:372"],"Definition":"A sporophyte development stage (PO:0028002) during which a sporophyte participates in multicellular organism senescence.","Source_ID":"PO:0007017","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"sporophyte senescent stage"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:435"],"Definition":"A leaf lamina vein (PO:0020138) arising from a quaternary (PO:0008022) or other higher order leaf vein.","Source_ID":"PO:0008023","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"higher order leaf vein"}
{"Definition":"A valve that is a part of a spore capsule that splits apart when the spore capsule dehisces.","Source_ID":"PO:0025229","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"spore capsule valve"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:359","pollen sac primary parietal cell layer"],"Definition":"A portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059) that is part of an anther wall (PO:0000002) and has as parts a primary parietal cell (PO:0006010) and adjacent plant cells.","Source_ID":"PO:0006006","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"anther wall primary parietal cell layer"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:517","E-L 1"],"Definition":"A bud development stage (PO:0025528) during which a bud (PO:0009006) participates in a bud dormancy process (GO:0097207).","Source_ID":"PO:0025529","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"bud dormancy stage"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:70","PO_GIT:280"],"Definition":"A plant structure (PO:0009011) that is the basal portion of a carpel (PO:0009030) or group of fused carpels and encloses the plant ovule(s) (PO:0020003).","Source_ID":"PO:0009072","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"plant ovary"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:339"],"Definition":"The shoot apex (PO:0000037) of the plant embryo (PO:0009009), above the cotyledonary node (PO:0025321).","Source_ID":"PO:0020032","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"plumule"}

{"Definition":"OBSOLETE. After the formation of the apical-basal axis in the young embryo, the central and basal portion give rise to the root meristem.","Source_ID":"PO:0007535","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"A1 root initials formation stage"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:149","portion of seed coat tissue"],"Definition":"A portion of plant tissue that is the covering of a seed derived from ovular - mainly integumentary - tissue.","Source_ID":"PO:0009088","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"seed coat"}

{"Definition":"A plant structure (PO:0009011) that is a uniseriate filament with positive geotropism that grows from an epidermis (PO:0005679) or protonema (PO:0030003).","Source_ID":"PO:0030078","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"rhizoid"}

{"Definition":"Empty upright ray cell of approximately the same height as the procumbent ray cell and occurring in indeterminate horizontal series usually interspersed among the procumbent cells.","Source_ID":"PO:0004530","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"tile cell"}
{"Definition":"A xylem sap (PO:0025539) that is located in the shoot system (PO:0009006).","Source_ID":"PO:0025565","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"shoot system xylem sap"}
{"Definition":"A plant ovule (PO:0020006) that is part of an ovuliferous scale (add).","Source_ID":"PO:0025491","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"ovuliferous scale ovule"}

{"Definition":"Elongated chlorenchymatous cell oriented perpendicular to the leaf surface and which is active in photosynthesis.","Source_ID":"PO:0006206","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"palisade mesophyll cell"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:264","paraclade"],"Definition":"An inflorescence axis (PO:0020122) that is a branch (PO:0009081) arising from a first order inflorescence axis (PO:0025104) or from a higher order inflorescence branch.","Source_ID":"PO:0009081","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"inflorescence branch"}
{"Definition":"A glume that is part of an ear spikelet.","Source_ID":"PO:0006367","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"glume of ear spikelet"}
{"Definition":"A multicellular glandular structure secreting a liquid containing organic substances especially sugars.","Source_ID":"PO:0009035","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"nectary"}
{"Definition":"OBSOLETE. The first phloem elements matures.","Source_ID":"PO:0007537","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"C3.2 maturation of phloem elements in root."}

{"Synonyms":["leaf, vascular","foliage leaf","vascular leaves","PO_GIT:137"],"Definition":"A leaf (PO:0025034) in a vascular plant.","Source_ID":"PO:0009025","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"vascular leaf"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:447","transition to heartwood stage"],"Definition":"A cell differentiation stage of secondary xylem (PO:0025469) that occurs during the interval between the first cell death of a tracheary element (PO:0000290) or non-septate xylem fiber cell (PO:0000274) and the death of the last secondary xylem parenchyma cell (PO:0004525) or septate fiber cell (PO:0004521) in a portion of secondary xylem (PO:0005848).","Source_ID":"PO:0025466","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"cell death stage of secondary xylem"}

{"Definition":"A root epidermal cell (PO:0025164) that develops from a trichoblast (PO:0000262) and has as part a root hair (GO:0035618).","Source_ID":"PO:0000256","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"root hair cell"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:49","PO_GIT:253"],"Definition":"A megasporangium (PO:0025201) in a seed plant, composed of fleshy subepidermal tissue that is part of a plant ovule (PO:0020003) and surrounds a megasporocyte (PO:0000431).","Source_ID":"PO:0020020","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"nucellus"}
{"Definition":"A locule that is a cavity in a fruit and develops from an ovary locule.","Source_ID":"PO:0025270","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"fruit locule"}

{"Definition":"OBSOLETE. A controlled vocabulary to describe the various plant parts and the growth and developmental stages.","Source_ID":"PO:0009075","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"plant ontology"}

{"Definition":"An axillary bud meristem (PO:0000232) that is part of a shoot axis tuber (PO:0004543).","Source_ID":"PO:0025068","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"shoot axis tuber axillary bud meristem"}

{"Definition":"A vascular system that includes the totality of the portions of vascular tissue in their specific arrangement in a stigma.","Source_ID":"PO:0008012","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"stigma vascular system"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:264","eighth order inflorescence axis  "],"Definition":"An inflorescence branch (PO:0009081) arising from a sixth order inflorescence branch (PO:0025108).","Source_ID":"PO:0025109","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"seventh order inflorescence branch"}
{"Definition":"OBSOLETE. A plant cell that is part of a male gametophyte.","Source_ID":"PO:0025027","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"microgametophytic cell"}
{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:220"],"Definition":"A portion of epidermis that is a sclerified outgrowth.","Source_ID":"PO:0025169","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"prickle"}
{"Definition":"The product of meiosis of the megaspore mother cell.","Source_ID":"PO:0007625","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"C tetrad of megaspores stage"}
{"Definition":"A prickle that is part of a shoot axis.","Source_ID":"PO:0025171","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"shoot axis prickle"}
{"Definition":"A substomatal cavity that is part of a phyllome.","Source_ID":"PO:0025398","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"phyllome substomatal cavity"}

{"Synonyms":["pistil primordium","portion of gynoecium primordium tissue","PO_GIT:465"],"Definition":"A floral structure primordium (PO:0025477) that is committed to the development of a gynoecium (PO:0009062).","Source_ID":"PO:0000019","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"gynoecium primordium"}
{"Definition":"Tissues that form specialized structures producing a secretion.","Source_ID":"PO:0005656","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"portion of secretory tissue"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:435"],"Definition":"A leaf lamina vein (PO:0020138) arising from a secondary leaf vein (PO:0020140).","Source_ID":"PO:0008021","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"tertiary leaf vein"}

{"Definition":"The chloroplast-containing, photosynthetic parenchymatous tissue situated between the two epidermal layers of the foliage leaf.","Source_ID":"PO:0005645","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"leaf mesophyll"}

{"Synonyms":["columella cells","PO_GIT:194","columella rootcap"],"Definition":"A portion of root parenchyma tissue that is the central part of a root cap in which the cells are arranged in longitudinal files.","Source_ID":"PO:0020130","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"central root cap"}

{"Synonyms":["leaf-derived cultured cell"],"Definition":"A cultured plant cell that was derived from leaf tissue.","Source_ID":"PO:0000007","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"leaf-derived cultured plant cell"}
{"Definition":"A central root cap that is part of a root cap of lateral root.","Source_ID":"PO:0003019","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"central root cap of lateral root"}

{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:455","wood parenchyma"],"Definition":"A portion of parenchyma (PO:0005421) tissue that is part of a portion of secondary xylem (PO:0005848) and has as parts secondary xylem parenchyma cells (PO:0004525).","Source_ID":"PO:0004532","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"secondary xylem parenchyma"}

{"Definition":"A portion of root exarch protoxylem (PO:0025555) tissue in which the primary xylem (PO:0005849) of the root system (PO:0025025) has two protoxylem strands or poles, and differentiation progresses centripetally, with the oldest elements (protoxylem) farthest from the center of the plant axis (PO:0025004).","Source_ID":"PO:0025559","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"diarch protoxylem"}
{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:360"],"Definition":"A phyllome tip (PO:0025141) that is part of a leaf apex (PO:0020137).","Source_ID":"PO:0025142","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"leaf tip"}

{"Synonyms":["shoot lateral growth meristem","PO_GIT:437"],"Definition":"A lateral meristem (PO:0020145) that is part of a shoot axis (PO:0025029).","Source_ID":"PO:0006344","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"shoot lateral meristem"}
{"Synonyms":["PO_GIT:366"],"Definition":"Shoot or leaf breaks through soil surface.","Source_ID":"PO:0007030","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"seedling shoot emergence stage"}
{"Definition":"The last mature leaf before the inflorescence in a cereal crop plant.","Source_ID":"PO:0020103","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"flag leaf"}

{"Definition":"An ear floret that is the upper of the two florets of a pedicellate spikelet rachilla of an ear inflorescence.","Source_ID":"PO:0006350","Source":"plant_ontology","Name":"upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear"}
